  "title": "Senior/Patent Engineer (Technology)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Patent Engineer</strong><br>\n</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Follow up on the project development progress of the Singapore-based R&amp;D team, identify core technologies, and explore the team’s patent portfolio.</li>\n  <li>Participate in the company’s international patent applications, especially in countries such as China, Europe, the United States, Japan, and South Korea.</li>\n  <li>Respond to Office Actions during the patent application process in the aforementioned countries.</li>\n  <li>Provide intellectual property training for the R&amp;D team and address IP-related inquiries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>3–5 years of experience in international patent applications.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with patent search, patent reviewing, patent portfolio management, and relevant patent laws and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Understand patent application processes and policies in China, the United States, Europe, Japan, and South Korea.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree or above, preferably in Computer Science, Automation, Vehicle Engineering, Electronics, or related fields</li>\n</ul>",
